**Minor:**
- **N1 — Stale tmpfile on encrypt failure.** Remote heredoc (script lines 142-151) creates `mktemp` then runs `systemd-creds encrypt`. If `encrypt` succeeds but `mv` fails (extremely unlikely on same-FS atomic rename), the `.iago-xxx.XXXXXX.cred` tmpfile remains in `/etc/credstore.encrypted/` (0700 root:root). No security impact; housekeeping debt only.
- **N2 — README §4 numbered list interrupted.** The chmod/exec-bit explanatory paragraph at line 59 sits between list items 3 and 4, breaking the auto-numbering in some markdown renderers. Cosmetic.

Both new findings are Minor and not blockers.

